<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...how to edit with the mouse?</b><br/><br/>
The use of mouse buttons:
<dl>
<dt>left</dt>
<dd>select <i>(if selector or edit button is on)<i><br></dd>
otherwise: insert a note <i>(only if a note button is on)</i><br>
or: insert an element <i>(like clef)</i> if a new element was choosen
<dt>middle</dt>
<dd>paste for block instructions</dd>
<dt>right</dt>
<dd>insert rest <i>(only if a note button is on)</i></dd>
<dt>Ctrl+left</dt>
<dd>delete</dd>
</dl>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...how to add and remove notes in chords?</b><br/>
<ul>
<li>to add a note to a chord make sure a note button is on and press left mouse button near this chord
<li>to remove a note press Ctrl + left mouse button near the note to be deleted
</ul>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...that you can move up/down inserted notes by means of the cursor up/down keys?</b>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...that you can insert bars with the <code>Tab</code> key?</b>
<br/><br/>
If configured NoteEdit inserts bars if you insert notes at the end. You
can insert your own bars by means of the Tab key. To check the bars produce a 2nd
staff with only rests and bars! If the bars are aligned, the measures are
complete.
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...how to edit with the keyboard?</b><br/><br/>
Some keys:
<dl>
<dt>Tab</dt>
<dd>insert bar</dd>
<dt>Backspace</dt>
<dd>delete</dd>
<dt>insert</dt>
<dd>edit mode</dd>
<dt>plus</dt>
<dd>sharp</dd>
<dt>equal</dt>
<dd>natural</dd>
<dt>minus</dt>
<dd>flat</dd>
</dl>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...how to use accidentals?</b><br/><br/>
Notes are inserted according keysig! So use the accidental buttons
(sharp, flat, natural) only if you wish a <i>visible</i> accidental.
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...that you can enable insert from keyboard mode?</b><br/><br/>
Activate the keyboard insertion mode by pressing the keyboard
insertion button. Then use the keys:
<dl>
<dt>enter</dt>
<dd>insert note</dd>
<dt>Ctrl+enter</dt>
<dd>add note to previous chord</dd>
<dt>backspace</dt>
<dd>delete note</dd>
<dt>Ctrl+backspace</dt>
<dd>delete note from previous chord</dd>
<dt>space</dt>
<dd>insert rest</dd>
<dt>Cursor up/down</dt>
<dd>determine pitch</dd>
</dl>
</html>
</tip>
