<tip category="NodeEdit|MIDI">
<html>
<b>...that you can determine the pitch by a MIDI keyboard connected to your
soundcard?</b><br/><br/>
Use the red keyboard button!
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|MIDI">
<html>
<b>...that you can record the notes from a MIDI keyboard connected to your
soundcard?</b><br/><br/>
Use the red record button.
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...that you can go to first/last measure by
<code>Alt + cursor left/right</code>?</b>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...that you can mark an arbitrary part of a staff to initiate block
commands?</b><br/><br/>
The block commands are:
<dl>
<dd>Backspace</dd>
<dt>delete block</dt>
<dd>middle mouse button</dd>
<dt>copy block to mouse pointer position</dt>
</dl>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...that you can give multistaff block commands?</b><br/><br/>
If you activate <code>Edit --&gt; Multistaff</code> the block commands
apply to all selected staves.
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...that you can select the whole staff by double click?</b>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...that you can create as many views as you want
(<code><u>W</u>indow --&gt; <u>N</u>ew Window</code>)?</b><br/><br/>
This allows you to copy between different scores.
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|MIDI">
<html>
<b>...that the MIDI import is performed by the TSE3 library when you select
<code>TSE3 --&gt; MIDI In</code>?</b><br/><br/>
To produce the score use
<code>TSE3 --&gt; filter dialog --&gt; TSE3 --&gt; Score</code>.
</html>
</tip>
