<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...that you can insert lines?</b><br/><br/>
Select <code>Insert --&gt; lines</code>, choose a line and left click on
a note.
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>...how to produce a audible (de-)crescendo?</b><br/><br/>
Place 2 different volume signatures	left and right the (de-)crescendo
symbol<br/>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>
...that Noteedit plays the <i>"post Mozart trill"</i>: dcdcdcdcdc...?
</b>
<br/><br/>
This is	also written to MIDI files.
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>
...that you can create multiple voices per staff ?
</b>
<p>choose: <code>Staff --&gt; Voices ... --&gt; Create voice</code></p>
<p>You should select:</p>
<ul>
<li> a preferred stem direction for the voice;
<li> a Y-position for the rests to make it possible to
     associate the rests to voices.
</ul>
<p>There is always a <i>current voice</i>. You can choose it
by means of the <i>voice counter</i>. <b>Note!</b> If the
voice counter displays an 'A' the <i>current voice</i> is the
first voice.</p>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>
...that you can transpose the staffs ?
</b>
<p>choose: <code>Tools --&gt; Transpose ... </code></p>
<p>Select the count of semitones! <b>Note!</b> It is
your resposibility to change the key signature!</p>
<p>If you want to transpose only a part of the staff
then mark the appropriate part before!</p>
<p>If you want to transpose a group of staffs then
select them before:</p
<p><code>Edit --&gt; Multistaff...</code></p>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="NodeEdit|General">
<html>
<b>
...that you can change the clef ?
</b>
<p>choose: <code>Tools --&gt; Change clef ... </code></p>
<p>Choose the new clef!</p>
<p>If you want to change the clef of only a part of the
staff then mark the appropriate part before!</p> 
<p><b>Note!</b> The marked range should begin with a
clef! Noteedit stops changing the chords/notes if a
new clef appears.</p>
</html>
</tip>
